Lagos State Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu has said the government is working on developing an infectious disease research centre, to enable researchers develop vaccines in response to future epidemic. He said the government is also working to make medical provisions ready for illnesses affecting citizens. The governor spoke yesterday in Alausa, Ikeja at the Lagos State Occupational Safety and Health Conference held to commemorate this year’s ‘World Day for Safety’.  Sanwo-Olu was represented by the Commissioner for Special Duties and Intergovernmental Relations, Tayo Bamgbose-Martins.  Lagos State Safety Commission  (LSSC) Director-General/CEO Mr. Lanre Mojola said the hazards of work-related accidents and illnesses, which were caused by unsafe conditions, acts and practices, necessitated the need for countries to put health and safety systems in place to change the narrative. 